  "claim_boundary": [
    "PKMAP2 extends the bounded PKMAP1 kernel leaves with one guarded stack and one read-only PBP1 range inside the same 2 MiB window.",
    "The candidate root clones the active UEFI PML4 and adds one private PML4/PDPT/PD/PT path only after proving the target root slot is empty.",
    "CR0.WP, CPU NX, and EFER.NXE are required; LA57, PCID, writable-executable leaves, overlap, and large kernel leaves fail closed.",
    "Every kernel, stack, and handoff leaf is independently walked; both stack guard indices must remain absent.",
    "The candidate CR3 is activated only for verification, with zero firmware calls, then the original CR3 is restored before firmware resumes.",
    "The private tables and mapped allocations remain retained through ExitBootServices, but the candidate CR3 is not activated as a final transfer state.",
    "Framebuffer equality proves no mapping drift from firmware state, not qualification of a final PooleOS cache policy.",
    "No kernel instruction, target-hardware transfer, N5 completion, signing, or production claim is made."
  ],
